              "CBI_Flag": 0,
              "Description": "Rumford Power is in compliance with OSHA Standard 29 CFR 1910.119, Process Safety Management of Highly Hazardous Chemicals.\n\nThe following engineering and administrative controls are in place to eliminate or reduce the possibility of an accidental release at the Rumford power facility:\n\n* Electronic ammonia detection, (3 detectors) installed in chiller building and safety relief valve stack. Detection system activates visual alarms at the facility main control center to alert personnel of a possible ammonia leak in the chiller system.\n* Ammonia detection is hard wired to ventilation system to activate exhaust fans in the event of a release in the chiller building.\n* Chiller System Controls monitor and control compressors, condenser, vessels and ammonia pumps. System displays continual operational status of equipment and controls alarms / shutdowns for out of  parameter indications. \n* High level alarms and system shut offs are installed on pressure vessels. Abnormal operating levels sensed in the vessels will activate a shutdown of the compressors.\n* Safety relief valves are configured to all pressure vessels to eliminate the potential for an over-pressure condition within the vessel and the refrigeration system.\n* Emergency stop button installed outside chiller building and in facility main control room to stop all ammonia refrigeration equipment and start exhaust fans in the event of a release.\n* Computerized \"MAXIMO\" preventative maintenance program is instituted within the maintenance department to ensure all chiller system components are maintained in optimum operational and mechancal condition.\n* Continual vibration analysis of compressors and condenser fans is provided to alert maintenance personnel of potential equipment malfunction, or failure.",
