      "FacilityID": 46794,
      "SummaryText": "The accidental release prevention and emergency response policy at Rumford Power is to comply with all applicable federal, state, and local laws and regulations. It is our goal to achieve and sustain \" Zero Accident Tolerance\" through communication, information, and training. If an emergency were to occur, it is our procedure to notify the Rumford Fire Department and request that they respond to the emergency.\n\nRumford Power is a combined cycle power plant. The regulated substances handled on location are Anhydrous Ammonia, which is used in the Chiller System as a coolant to enhance gas turbine performance and efficiency. The second regulated substance is Aqueous Ammonia, which is used in the Selective Catalytic Reduction system to reduce nitrous oxide emissions from the power plant."
